Policy.acknowledgement_statement: Collection of these data were supported by the National Cancer Institute at the National Institutes of Health (1R01CA134786 to WC and CAH, 2P50CA100707 to KCA, Myeloma SPORE 2P50CA100707 Project 6 to KCA, WC and DVC, R01CA152336, P50 CA142509 and R01CA184464 to RZO, and R21CA191896 and K24CA169004 to EZ). The study also received support from the Steve and Nancy Grand Multiple Myeloma Translational Initiative to EZ. Data collection from the cancer registries was supported by the National Cancer Institute Surveillance Epidemiology and End Results Population-based Registry Program, National Institutes of Health, Department of Health and Human Services, under contracts N01-PC-35139 (contract HHSN261201300021I) to USC for Los Angeles County and No. N01-PC-2013-00021 (contract HHSN261201300021I) to the New Jersey State Cancer Registry), and from the National Program of Cancer Registries of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (NU5U58DP003931-05-00 -HHSN261201300016I to the New Jersey State Cancer Registry, HHSN26100015 to the Louisiana Tumor Registry at Louisiana State University, HHSN261201300011I to Wayne State University and 1U58DP000807-01 to the California Cancer Registry), and by the University of Southern California Norris Comprehensive Cancer Center Core grant P30CA014089 and the Johns Hopkins University Sidney Kimmel Cancer Center from the National Cancer Institute Core grant P30CA006973, and the State of New Jersey and the Rutgers Cancer Institute of New Jersey. The collection of patients used in this publication was supported in part by the California Department of Health Services as part of the statewide cancer reporting program mandated by California Health and Safety Code Section 103885.

GSR_Access.gsr_mode_label: Controlled-access (GSR are sensitive according to the Institutional Certification)

ConsentGroup.title: General Research Use
ConsentGroup.name: GRU
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Use of the data is limited only by the terms of the model Data Use Certification.

ConsentGroup.title: Health/Medical/Biomedical (IRB, NPU)
ConsentGroup.name: HMB-IRB-NPU
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Use of this data is limited to health/medical/biomedical purposes, does not include the study of population origins or ancestry. Requestor must provide documentation of local IRB approval. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations.

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Multiple Myeloma, MDS)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-MM-MDS
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Use of the data must be related to Multiple Myeloma. Use of the data includes methods development research (e.g., development of software or algorithms).

ConsentGroup.title: General Research Use (NPU)
ConsentGroup.name: GRU-NPU
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction: Use of the data is limited only by the terms of the model Data Use Certification. Use of the data is limited to not-for-profit organizations.

ConsentGroup.title: Disease-Specific (Cancer, PUB)
ConsentGroup.name: DS-CA-PUB
ConsentGroup.Use-Restriction:
Use of the data must be related to Cancer. Requestor agrees to make results of studies using the data available to the larger scientific community.
General methods development research is NOT allowed.
